{A43: Schmid Benoni} 1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 c5 3. Bf4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 (4. Bxb8 Qa5+ 5. c3
Rxb8 6. Qxd4 Nf6 7. Nbd2 (7. e3 e6 8. Nbd2 a6 9. Bd3 Qc7 10. O-O b5 11. Rfe1
Bb7 12. a4 Bc5 13. Qh4 Bc6 14. axb5 axb5 15. Nd4 Bd7 16. e4 Be7 17. exd5 Nxd5
18. Qg4 g6 19. Qf3 O-O 20. Be4 Nb6 21. Bc6 Nc4 {Harakis,A (2220)-Greet,A (2449)
England 2012 0-1 (38)}) 7... e6 8. Nb3 Qb6 9. Qxb6 axb6 10. e3 Bd6 11. Bb5+ Ke7
12. O-O Ra8 13. c4 dxc4 14. Bxc4 Bd7 15. Nbd2 {1/2-1/2 (15) Sokolov,A (2580)
-Westerinen,H (2410) Gausdal 1996}) 4... f6 $146 {Prevents intrusion on e5+g5}
(4... Nc6 5. e3 e6 6. Be2 Nf6 7. O-O Be7 8. Bf3 O-O 9. c4 Qb6 10. Nc3 Nxd4 11.
Qxd4 Qxd4 12. exd4 dxc4 13. Rac1 Rd8 14. Nb5 a6 15. Nc7 Ra7 16. Rxc4 b5 17. Rc2
Bb7 18. Bxb7 Rxb7 19. Be5 {Singer,R (2210)-Meszaros,A (2390) Zalaegerszeg 1993
0-1}) 5. Nf3 (5. Bd2 $5 $11) 5... e5 $15 {Black threatens to win material:
e5xf4} 6. Bg3 Nc6 7. e3 {Secures d4} Qb6 8. b3 (8. Nc3 Be6 9. Nxd5 Qa5+ 10. Nc3
Bb4 $15) 8... Bf5 (8... Be6 $5 $17) 9. Be2 Nb4 {[%cal Rb4c2,Rf5c2,Gd1c2]
Exerts pressure on the backward pawn} 10. e4 $2 (10. O-O $142 {and White hangs
on} Nxc2 11. Nh4 $15) 10... Bxe4 11. Bd3 $2 (11. O-O Nxc2 12. Nc3 Nxa1 13. Bb5+
Kd8 14. Ba4 $17) 11... Bxd3 12. cxd3 Rc8 13. Na3 (13. O-O {does not save the
day} Nc2 14. Nbd2 Nxa1 15. Qxa1 Bd6 $19) 13... Qa5 14. O-O Qxa3 15. Nxe5 (15.
Re1 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game} Ne7 16. Bxe5 Nc2 $19)
15... Ne7 (15... fxe5 $142 {makes sure everything is clear} 16. Qh5+ Kd8 17.
Bxe5 Nxd3 18. Bd4 $19) 16. Nf3 Nf5 17. Qe2+ Kf7 18. Rae1 (18. Rfe1 {hardly
improves anything} Qa6 19. Nh4 Nxh4 $19) 18... Qa6 19. Nh4 Nxh4 20. Bxh4 (20.
Qg4 {cannot change what is in store for White} f5 21. Qxh4 Nxd3 22. Rd1 $19)
20... Bc5 (20... h5 {might be the shorter path} 21. Bg3 $19) 21. Qh5+ $4 {
White crumbles in face of a dire situation} (21. a3 $142 Qc6 22. axb4 Bxb4 23.
Rb1 $19) 21... g6 $19 22. Qf3 Rhd8 23. Bg5 (23. Re2 {doesn't get the cat off
the tree} Bd4 $19) 23... Nxd3 (23... Nc2 {keeps an even firmer grip} 24. Re5
$19) 24. Re2 Rc6 (24... Bd4 $5 {and Black can already relax} 25. Rd2 Rc3 26.
Be3 $19) 25. Rd1 Nb4 26. Rde1 (26. a4 {does not improve anything} d4 27. Bc1 d3
$19) 26... Qd3 27. Bd2 Qxf3 28. gxf3 Nd3 29. Rd1 Re6 30. Rxe6 Kxe6 31. Ba5 (31.
Kf1 {is no salvation} Nxf2 32. Rc1 Bd4 $19) 31... b6 (31... Nxf2 {makes it
even easier for Black} 32. Re1+ Kd7 33. Kf1 $19) 32. Bxb6 axb6 33. Rxd3 Ra8 34.
a4 Ke5 35. Rd1 (35. Kf1 {doesn't change anything anymore} d4 36. Ke2 Kd5 $19)
35... d4 36. Kf1 Kd5 (36... Bb4 {seems even better} 37. Ke2 Rc8 38. f4+ Kd5 39.
f5 $19) 37. f4 (37. Ke2 {does not win a prize} Bd6 $19) 37... Re8 38. Kg2 Bb4
39. Rd3 (39. f5 $19 {what else?}) 39... Ke4 40. Rf3 Bd2 (40... Rd8 $142 {
and Black takes home the point} 41. h4 $19) 41. Rh3 h5 42. Rg3 g5 43. fxg5 fxg5
44. Rh3 h4 45. Rf3 Bf4 46. b4 d3 (46... d3 47. Rxd3 Kxd3 $19) 0-1

