threatens to win material: b5xc4} 8. Ba2 Nd4 (8... Nge7 9. O-O $11) 9. O-O (9.
e5 Ne7 10. Ne4 O-O $14) 9... Nxf3+ (9... Bb7 $5 $11 {is an interesting idea})
10. Qxf3 $14 (10. gxf3 $6 Bd4+ 11. Kg2 Ne7 $11) 10... Bb7 {Black should
quickly conclude development.} 11. f5 (11. Qf2 $142 $16) 11... exf5 $4 {
Black lets it slip away} (11... gxf5 $142 {would keep Black in the game} 12.
Qf4 Ne7 $17) 12. Qg3 Ne7 13. Bg5 (13. exf5 $142 Qb6 14. fxg6 c4+ 15. Be3 Qxg6
16. dxc4 $16) 13... O-O $4 (13... Bd4+ $142 {is just about the only chance} 14.
Kh1 f6 $14) 14. exf5 Nxf5 $6 {Black seems to have resigned himself to defeat..}
(14... h6 15. fxg6 hxg5 16. Bxf7+ Rxf7 17. gxf7+ Kf8 $18) 15. Rxf5 Qb6 16. Rff1
(16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. Rxd5 (17. Bxd5 $143 gxf5 18. Bxa8 Rxa8 $11) 17... c4+ 18. Be3
$18) 16... d5 (16... Rae8 17. Rae1 Rxe1 18. Rxe1 b4 $18) 17. Nxd5 Bxd5 18. Bxd5
Ra7 19. c3 (19. Rae1 $142 {keeps an even firmer grip} c4+ 20. Be3 Bd4 21. dxc4
bxc4 $18) 19... Kh8 (19... Rd7 {hardly improves anything} 20. Qf3 $18) 20. Rae1
f6 (20... Rd7 {doesn't change the outcome of the game} 21. Be7 Rxd5 22. Bxf8
Bxf8 23. Rxf7 c4+ 24. d4 $18) 21. Bf4 Rd7 (21... g5 {doesn't change the
outcome of the game} 22. Bd6 Rd8 23. Re6 $18) 22. Be6 (22. Re6 {makes it even
easier for White} Qd8 23. Bd6 Rg8 $18) 22... c4+ (22... Rb7 {cannot undo what
has already been done} 23. Rf3 $18) 23. d4 Re7 (23... Rb7 {doesn't improve
anything} 24. Bd5 Rd7 25. Re6 $18) 24. Bd6 Ree8 25. Bxf8 Rxe6 (25... Rxf8 {
