{D02: 1 d4 d5 2 Nf3 sidelines, including 2...Nf6 3 g3 and 2...Nf6 3 Bf4} 1. d4
d5 2. Bf4 Bf5 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Nbd2 Bd6 6. c3 (6. Bg3 c5 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8.
Bxb8 Rxb8 9. Bb5+ Ke7 10. Bd3 Bg6 11. Qe2 Qb6 12. Rb1 Rhd8 13. O-O Rbc8 14.
Rfc1 a5 15. a3 a4 16. Bxg6 hxg6 17. c4 Qa6 18. Kf1 d4 19. exd4 Bxd4 20. b4 axb3
{Cyborowski,L (2450)-Miladinovic,I (2519) Ohrid 2001 1-0 (39)}) 6... Bxf4 $146
(6... O-O 7. Qb3 Bxf4 8. exf4 c5 9. Be2 Qc7 10. g3 Ne4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Nh4
cxd4 13. Nxf5 exf5 14. cxd4 Nc6 15. Rd1 Rfd8 16. d5 Qa5+ 17. Kf1 Nb4 18. a3
Nxd5 19. Bc4 Nf6 20. Bxf7+ Kh8 21. Kg2 {Labeckas,K (2348)-Bastys,R (2236)
Vilnius 2014 1/2-1/2 (31)}) 7. exf4 O-O {Black castles and improves king safety
} 8. Qe2 (8. Be2 Nbd7 $11) 8... h6 {Prevents intrusion on g5} (8... Nbd7 9. Qd1
$15) 9. h3 {Consolidates g4} c6 10. Ne5 Nbd7 11. Nxd7 (11. Qe3 Qb6 12. b3 c5
$15) 11... Qxd7 (11... Nxd7 12. Qe3 $15) 12. f3 {Controls e4} (12. g4 Bg6 $11)
12... Qc7 13. g3 Qb6 {Black threatens to win material: Qb6xb2} 14. O-O-O (14.
Nb3 Nd7 $17) 14... Rac8 (14... Qa5 $5 15. a3 Qa4 $17) 15. g4 $15 {White
threatens to win material: g4xf5} Bh7 16. Bg2 $2 (16. Nb3 $142 $5 $15 {would
keep White alive}) 16... c5 (16... Qa5 $142 17. a3 Qa4 $19) 17. f5 $4 {an
oversight. But White was lost anyway.} (17. Nb3 c4 18. Na1 Qa5 $17) 17... exf5
(17... cxd4 $142 {seems even better} 18. Nb1 dxc3 19. bxc3 exf5 20. Qb2 $19)
18. gxf5 $4 {White crumbles in face of a dire situation} (18. dxc5 Qa5 19. a3
$19) 18... Bxf5 (18... cxd4 $5 {makes it even easier for Black} 19. Qf2 dxc3
