Bxf4 9. exf4 Nc6 10. c3 {Secures b4} f5 11. gxf6 Qxf6 12. Ne2 Bd7 {[%cal Ye7f5,
Yc6e7,Yd7c6,Yc8d7] Manoeuvre Nc8-d7-c6-e7-f5} 13. Qc2 {White threatens to win
material: Qc2xe4} O-O-O 14. Bxe4 Ne7 15. O-O-O (15. Bxh7 $2 {is no good} g6 16.
Bxg6 Nxg6 $19 (16... Qxg6 $6 17. Qxg6 Nxg6 18. Rg1 $19)) 15... Bc6 16. Bxc6
Nxc6 17. Qe4 Ne7 18. Rhg1 g6 19. Rg5 Nf5 {A comfortable square for the black
knight} 20. Rgg1 Rhf8 (20... Ne7 21. Rd3 $16) 21. Rd3 $14 Rd5 22. Kb1 Nd6 23.
Qe3 Nc4 {Black threatens to win material: Nc4xe3} 24. Qh3 Qf5 (24... Rh5 25.
Qg2 $11) 25. Kc2 {White king safety dropped} (25. b3 Na5 $16) 25... Ra5 26.
Qxf5 {White forks: e6+f8} Rfxf5 27. Kb1 Rab5 28. b3 Rh5 29. h3 Nd6 30. Re3 {
White threatens to win material: Re3xe6} Kd7 31. Kc2 Nf5 32. Rd3 Rd5 33. Rg5
Ne7 34. Rdg3 (34. Re5 $5 $16) 34... Rdxg5 $11 35. fxg5 Nf5 {Black threatens to
win material: Nf5xg3} 36. Rf3 Rxg5 37. Ng3 h5 (37... Nxg3 38. fxg3 Rf5 39. Rxf5
exf5 40. Kd3 $11) 38. Ne4 {White threatens to win material: Ne4xg5} Rg2 39.
Nc5+ {White forks: b7} Ke7 40. Nxb7 g5 (40... Nh4 41. Rd3 $11) 41. Nc5 g4 42.
hxg4 hxg4 43. Rf4 g3 {Black threatens to win material: g3xf2} 44. Ne4 $4 {
releasing the pressure on the opponent} (44. Kd3 gxf2 45. Ne4 f1=Q+ 46. Rxf1
Rxa2 47. Nc5 $16) 44... Ne3+ $4 {allows the opponent back into the game} (44...
Rh2 $142 45. Nxg3 Nxg3 $17) 45. Kd3 $16 Nd5 46. Rf3 gxf2 47. Rxf2 Rg1 48. Nc5 {
White threatens to win material: Nc5xa6} (48. Rh2 $142 $5 $16) 48... Rg3+ $14 {
Black skewers: c3} 49. Kd2 Nxc3 50. a4 a5 {White has a new backward pawn: b3} (
50... Kd6 51. Rf8 $14) 51. Rh2 $14 Kd6 52. Rh6 (52. Rh5 Rf3 $16) 52... Nb1+ (
52... Kd5 53. Nxe6 Ne4+ 54. Kc2 Rg2+ 55. Kc1 $11) 53. Kc2 $14 {White threatens
to win material: Kc2xb1} Na3+ $4 (53... Nc3 $142 $14 {this is the best bet to
save the position}) 54. Kb2 $18 Kd5 55. Nxe6 Nc4+ (55... Nb1 56. Nf4+ Ke4 57.
Ne2 $18 (57. Kxb1 $6 {is clearly worse} Kxf4 58. Kb2 Ke4 $14)) 56. bxc4+ Kxc4
57. Rh5 Rg2+ 58. Kc1 Kb4 (58... Rg6 {does not save the day} 59. Rc5+ Kb4 $18)
59. Nc5 (59. d5 $142 $18 {and White has it in the bag}) 59... Kc3 60. Rh3+ Kxd4
61. Ne6+ (61. Nb7 Kc4 62. Kb1 Kb4 63. Rh4+ Ka3 $18) 61... Kc4 $16 62. Nxc7 Kb4
(62... Rg4 63. Nb5 Kb4 $11) 63. Rh4+ Kb3 64. Nb5 $4 {lets it slip away} (64.
Nd5 $142 $18 {secures victory}) 64... Ra2 {[%cal Ra2a4,Rb3a4,Gh4a4] Attacks
the isolani on a4. Black threatens to win material: Ra2xa4} 65. Rh3+ Kb4 66.
Nc3 {White threatens to win material: Nc3xa2} Rg2 67. Kb1 Rf2 $4 (67... Kb3
$142 $11 {would save the game}) 68. Nd1 $18 Rg2 $2 (68... Rf1 69. Rh4+ Kb3 $18)
69. Rh4+ (69. Nb2 $142 $18 {and the rest is a matter of technique}) 69... Kb3
$11 70. Rd4 Rh2 71. Kc1 Rc2+ 72. Kb1 Rh2 {Twofold repetition} 73. Rf4 Rg2 74.
Ne3 {White threatens to win material: Ne3xg2} Re2 {Black has a mate threat} 75.
Nd1 Rg2 76. Kc1 1/2-1/2

