{A47: 1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 b6: Torre, London and Colle Systems} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 e6
3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. Nbd2 d6 6. Bd3 Nbd7 7. h3 (7. Qe2 Nd5 8. c3 Nxf4 9. exf4
g6 10. h4 Nf6 11. Ne4 Bg7 12. g3 Qd7 13. a4 O-O 14. Nxf6+ Bxf6 15. Be4 c5 16.
O-O cxd4 17. cxd4 Rac8 18. a5 Bxe4 19. Qxe4 Qb5 20. axb6 axb6 21. Rfd1 Rc4 {
Stripunsky,A (2563)-Benjamin,J (2552) ICC INT 2011 1/2-1/2 (76)}) 7... Be7 (
7... Qe7 8. Bg3 g6 9. O-O Bg7 10. a4 a6 11. a5 b5 12. c4 e5 13. dxe5 dxe5 14.
Be2 b4 15. Qc2 Nh5 16. Bh4 Bf6 17. Bxf6 Nhxf6 18. c5 Nxc5 19. Rfc1 Nfd7 20. Nb3
Nxb3 21. Qxb3 c5 22. Bc4 {Khotenashvili,B (2504)-Cramling,P (2518) Beijing
2014 0-1 (69)}) 8. c3 a6 $146 {Prevents intrusion on b5} (8... O-O 9. Qe2 Re8
10. Bh2 Bf8 11. e4 e5 12. d5 a5 13. Bb5 Re7 14. a4 g6 15. g4 Bg7 16. Bg3 Nb8
17. Bd3 Ba6 18. Bxa6 Nxa6 19. Nh2 Nc5 20. h4 Qc8 21. f3 Qa6 22. Qxa6 Rxa6 23.
Ke2 {Rakhmanov,A (2473)-Kiselev,V (2277) playchess.com INT 2006 1-0 (100)}) (
8... c5 9. O-O $14) 9. O-O $16 c5 (9... O-O 10. e4 $14) 10. Qe2 (10. Ng5 O-O
$14) 10... b5 (10... Qc7 11. a4 $14) 11. e4 (11. a4 $5 c4 12. Bc2 $16) 11... c4
{Black gets more space} 12. Bc2 h6 {Secures g5} 13. e5 (13. b3 cxb3 14. axb3
Qc7 $16) 13... dxe5 $14 14. dxe5 Nd5 15. Bh2 O-O 16. Qe4 g6 17. Qg4 h5 {
Black threatens to win material: h5xg4} 18. Qg3 Kg7 (18... Nc5 $5 $11) 19. Nd4
Bg5 $4 (19... Nc5 $142 {and Black is still in the game} 20. Ne4 Nxe4 21. Bxe4
Qb6 $14) 20. h4 {Deflection: f8} Bxd2 (20... Bxh4 21. Nxe6+ {Deflection}) 21.
Nxe6+ $1 {Deflection: g6} Kh6 (21... fxe6 22. Qxg6+ {Mate attack Deflection})
22. Nxd8 Raxd8 23. e6 $1 {Deflection: g6} Bf4 (23... fxe6 24. Qxg6# {Mate
attack Deflection}) 24. Qf3 (24. Qxf4+ $142 {makes sure everything is clear}
Nxf4 25. Bxf4+ (25. exd7 $6 {is a weaker possibility} Ne2+ 26. Kh1 Rxd7 $14)
25... Kg7 26. e7 $18) 24... fxe6 25. Bxf4+ (25. Qe4 {seems even better} Bxh2+
26. Kxh2 Rf5 $18) 25... Rxf4 26. Qe2 e5 (26... Rxh4 27. Qxe6 Rg4 $18) 27. Rad1
Rxh4 (27... Kg7 $18 {the only chance to get some counterplay}) 28. Rxd5 $1 {
Decoy: d5} Bxd5 29. Qd2+ g5 (29... Rf4 {what else?} 30. g3 Nf6 31. gxf4 e4 $18)
30. Qxd5 Rg4 31. Bf5 (31. Qe6+ Kg7 32. Qe7+ Kg8 33. Qxd8+ Nf8 34. Qd5+ Ne6 35.
Qxe6+ Kf8 36. Bg6 Rf4 37. Rd1 b4 38. Rd7 Rxf2 39. Qe8#) 31... Rf4 32. Bxd7 (32.
Bxd7 Rdf8 33. Qxe5 $18) 1-0

