-Manik,M (2447) Presov 1999}) (11. h3 Bc8 $16) 11... Bxf6 $14 {Black has the
pair of bishops} 12. h3 {White threatens to win material: h3xg4} Be6 13. Nd5
Bxd5 14. Rxd5 ({Inferior is} 14. exd5 Nd7 $11) 14... Nc6 15. Bb5 Red8 (15...
Re6 16. Rd7 a6 17. Ba4 $14) 16. Bxc6 $16 bxc6 17. Rxd8+ (17. Rc5 Rab8 $16)
17... Rxd8 $14 18. Kf1 Bg7 19. Ke2 f6 {Covers g5} 20. Rd1 Rxd1 21. Kxd1 {
A minor pieces endgame occured} Kf7 22. Ke2 Bh6 23. Ne1 Ke6 24. Kd3 Bf8 25. Kc4
h6 26. Nd3 f5 27. f4 (27. Nc5+ $5 Ke7 28. b4 $16) 27... fxe4 $11 28. Nxe5 {
White forks: c6+g6} Kf5 29. Kd4 $4 {letting the wind out of his own sails} (29.
g3 c5 30. Ng4 c6 $11) 29... Bd6 (29... Bg7 $142 {would have given Black the
upper hand} 30. Ke3 Bxe5 31. fxe5 Kxe5 $19) 30. Nxc6 $11 Kxf4 31. Nxa7 (31. h4
$142 $11) 31... Kg3 $4 {Black threatens to win material: Kg3xg2. gives the
opponent counterplay} (31... Be5+ $142 32. Kc4 Bxb2 $17) 32. Nb5 Bf4 (32... e3
33. Kxe3 (33. Nxd6 $4 {would be gruesome error} e2 34. Ne4+ Kxg2 $19) 33...
Bc5+ 34. Ke4 $18) 33. Kxe4 g5 (33... Bd2 34. Nxc7 Kxg2 35. c4 $18) 34. a4 c6 $2
(34... c5 35. a5 Kxg2 36. h4 $18) 35. Nd4 Bc7 (35... Kxg2 36. a5 (36. Nxc6 $6
Kxh3 37. a5 Bc7 $18) 36... Bc7 37. b4 Kxh3 38. a6 $18) 36. Kf5 Kxg2 37. Kg4 Bf4
(37... c5 38. Nc6 Kf2 39. a5 $18) 38. Ne6 (38. a5 {might be the shorter path}
h5+ 39. Kxh5 Bc7 $18) 38... Bd2 (38... Be3 39. a5 Ba7 40. c3 $18) 39. c3 Be3 (
39... h5+ {cannot change destiny} 40. Kxh5 Kxh3 41. Nxg5+ Kg3 42. Ne4+ Kf4 43.
Nxd2 $18) 40. b4 (40. a5 Ba7 41. Nd4 $18) 40... h5+ (40... Bb6 $18 {is still a
small chance}) 41. Kxh5 Kxh3 (41... Ba7 {cannot change what is in store for
White} 42. a5 Kg3 43. Kxg5 $18) 42. Nxg5+ (42. Nxg5+ Kg3 43. Ne6 $18) 1-0

