g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. c4 d6 6. d3 c6 7. Nc3 e5 8. Rb1 Nbd7 9. b4 Qc7 (
9... d5 10. b5 dxc4 11. dxc4 Qa5 12. Qb3 Re8 13. Ng5 Nb8 14. Nce4 Qc7 15. Ba3
Nxe4 16. Nxe4 Rd8 17. Rfd1 Rxd1+ 18. Rxd1 cxb5 19. cxb5 Nd7 20. Rc1 {1-0 (20)
Vidit,S (2565)-Narayanan,S (2483) Kocaeli 2013}) 10. b5 Nc5 11. bxc6 bxc6 12.
Na4 $146 (12. Ba3 Nfd7 13. Nd2 f5 14. Nb5 cxb5 15. Bxa8 Nb6 16. Bg2 Nba4 17.
Qc2 e4 18. dxe4 Nc3 19. Rbe1 fxe4 20. Nb1 Nxb1 21. Rxb1 Bf5 22. g4 Bxg4 23.
Bxc5 dxc5 24. Qxe4 Bf5 25. Qd5+ Kh8 26. Rxb5 Be5 {Leer Salvesen,B (2261)
-Ornstein,P (2223) Gausdal 2000 1-0}) (12. Be3 Ne6 $14) 12... Ne6 $11 13. Bd2
Bd7 14. Nc3 Rfb8 15. Rxb8+ Rxb8 16. Qc2 d5 17. cxd5 cxd5 {Black has an active
position.} 18. Rc1 d4 {Black threatens to win material: d4xc3} 19. Ne4 Qxc2 20.
Nxf6+ Bxf6 21. Rxc2 Rb1+ 22. Rc1 Rxc1+ (22... Rb2 23. a3 $15) 23. Bxc1 $11 {
A minor pieces endgame occured} Bg7 24. Ba3 f6 {Secures g5} 25. Nd2 Nc7 {
[%cal Yd5c3,Yc7d5,Ye6c7] The knight aims for Ne6-c7-d5-c3} 26. Bc5 Be6 27. a4
a6 28. Bd6 {White threatens to win material: Bd6xc7} (28. f4 exf4 29. gxf4 f5
$11) 28... Nd5 29. Ne4 Nc3 {Black threatens to win material: Nc3xa4. Black
forks: a4+e2. Black can be proud of that piece} 30. Nc5 {White threatens to
win material: Nc5xe6. White forks: a6+e6} Bc8 (30... Nxe2+ $2 {doesn't work
because of} 31. Kf1 Bg4 32. h3 Nxg3+ 33. fxg3 $18) 31. Bf3 Bf8 32. Bxf8 Kxf8
33. a5 Ke7 34. Nb3 $2 (34. Kf1 $142 $11 {and White could well hope to play on})
34... Kd6 $17 35. Kf1 Be6 36. Nd2 Bd5 (36... Kc5 $142 $5 37. Ba8 Kb4 $17) 37.
Bxd5 $15 Kxd5 {A knight endgame occured} 38. Nc4 Na2 39. Ke1 Nb4 40. Nb6+ Kc6
41. Nc4 Kb5 42. Nb6 (42. g4 $5 $15 {is an interesting alternative}) 42... Kxa5
$17 43. Nd7 Nd5 44. Nf8 $2 (44. Kd2 $142 $17) 44... Kb4 $19 45. Kd2 Kb3 46. Kc1
(46. f4 exf4 47. Ne6 Kb2 48. Nxd4 a5 49. gxf4 a4 $19) 46... Nc3 (46... a5 $5 {
keeps an even firmer grip} 47. Ne6 a4 48. Nc5+ Kb4 49. Nd7 $19) 47. e3 a5 48.
exd4 exd4 49. Ne6 Nb5 50. Kd2 $4 {leading to a quick end} (50. Nc5+ Kc3 $19)
50... a4 (50... Kb2 $142 {ends the debate} 51. Nc5 Nc3 $19) 51. Nc5+ Kb4 52.
Na6+ Ka5 53. Nc5 (53. Nb8 $19) 53... a3 (53... Nc7 $142 $19 {Black has a
promising position}) 54. Kc2 $17 Kb4 55. Na6+ Ka4 1/2-1/2

